content: Love it! The only thing I wish was different is that instead of having to add each bag, you could select how many ounces you stored total and then put how many bags they're in.

The feature estimating how long the milk can last your baby is also very useful. content: The calculation is off. I put in all my milk I have saved up, set my settings and set it to ounces. Said I had 11 days worth of milk. I switch it to MLs, not changing, adding, or deleting information and suddenly I have enough milk to last juuussst under a year. Makes no sense. Waste of my time.
replyContent:
Hi Amber, when you change your settings from oz to mL, you also need to change your "amounts fed" setting, since it will still have the default oz amounts. You can do so by going to Settings>Amounts Fed, clicking "Restore Defaults" and saving. Then when you recalculate your stats, it should be what you're expecting. Hope  that helps!
-Jennifer
